cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with the application of deep learning techniques for medical image analysis, specifically for cardiac segmentation and disease diagnosis. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also proposes a novel dual loss function, which falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of deep learning for medical image analysis also falls under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the potential clinical applications of the proposed approach, which falls under the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
